We must bear in mind the circumstance, to which we have already adverted in the Prolegomena, that the distribution of the dialogus among tbe different characters rests in many cases solely upon the discretion of the mediaeval transcriber or modern r editor, for it appears certain that in the MS. which was the archetype , of those now existing, the change from one speaker to another was indicated merely by a blank space, the name of the speaker not having been inserted. Indeed, in the best existing MS. of Plautus, the Vetus Codex of Camerarius, the space for the names is left blank in some of the plays.
